teximage.text: $$ \textbf{Putnam 1998, B-2} \\ \\ \begin{aligned} &\text{Given a point } (a,b) \text{ with } 0<b<a. \text{ determine the minimum perimeter of a} \\ &\text{triangle with one vertex at } (a, b), \text{ one vertex on the } x\text{-axis, and one vertex on} \\ &\text{the line } y=x. \text{ You may assume that a triangle of minimum perimeter exists.} \end{aligned} $$
